# Campaign Defaults Pin — driven single-issue test entry
#
# Deployment-time pin for the driven `RUN_SINGLE_ISSUE` entry point.
# When req_dispatcher drives a single issue, the trigger (I1) carries ONLY
# {project, iid, correlation_id, dispatcher_callback_target, group?}. Every
# other campaign field — branch / quota / concurrency / timeouts / repo
# layout — is read from THIS file, never from the trigger. dispatch_single_issue.sh
# (Task A2) sources this file to synthesize the campaign env equivalent to a
# RUN_SCHEDULED_ISSUE_CAMPAIGN with issue_iids=[iid].
#
# This file is `source`d (and may be loaded under `set -a`), so keep it pure
# `KEY=value` lines — NO shell logic, NO command substitution, NO conditionals.
#
# Trigger inputs do NOT override these values on the driven path. Edit this
# file only when the deployment genuinely changes the pinned campaign shape.
# See config/README.md §campaign_defaults.env for per-field rationale.

# ─── Branch model (see CLAUDE.md §Two-branch model) ───────────────
# Integration / MR target branch. MRs are opened against this branch.
BRANCH=master
# Clean baseline + shared-config source branch. Fresh-mode attempts reset the
# per-issue worktree to origin/${DEV_BRANCH}. Set equal to BRANCH to disable.
DEV_BRANCH=dev

# ─── Driven single-issue invariants (quota=1 / concurrency=1) ─────
# Per-tick launch quota. The driven path tests exactly ONE issue per trigger,
# so this is pinned to 1 (one IID dispatched, one subagent in flight).
HOURLY_ISSUE_QUOTA=1
# Max concurrent subagents = batch-size cap. Pinned to 1 on the driven path:
# the single driven IID is the only thing in flight, so no cross-IID
# parallelism is needed and the UI-account pool (if any) divides into 1 slot.
MAX_CONCURRENT_SUBAGENTS=1

# ─── UI test accounts ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cap on how many UI accounts ONE IID receives after the pool is divided by
# MAX_CONCURRENT_SUBAGENTS. Matches the dispatcher default (14).
MAX_ACCOUNTS_PER_ISSUE=14
# Relative path (under the project checkout root) of the UI test-account pool
# file. EMPTY by default: UI accounts are opt-in. When empty the dispatcher
# skips the entire UI-account flow and the rendered prompt omits its
# `# UI test accounts` section. A deployment that needs UI accounts pins the
# relpath here (e.g. ifp-data/ifp-common/ifp_users.json).
UI_ACCOUNTS_RELPATH=

# ─── Timeouts (seconds) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# acpx exec wall-clock cap for one attempt. On overrun the attempt is parked
# as terminal `timeout` (never auto-retried).
ACPX_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=18000
# Subagent runtime cap passed to sessions_spawn as runTimeoutSeconds. Kept
# slightly above ACPX_TIMEOUT_SECONDS (acpx cap + 120) so the runtime does not
# kill the subagent before acpx's own timeout flow runs.
RUN_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=18120

# ─── Repo layout (see env_paths.sh derivation) ───────────────────
# Basename of the agent runtime root inside the project checkout. env_paths.sh
# derives RESULT_ROOT=${REPO_PATH}/${RESULT_BASENAME}.
RESULT_BASENAME=ifp-result
# Basename of the test team's knowledge-base directory inside the checkout.
# env_paths.sh derives DATA_DIR=${REPO_PATH}/${DATA_BASENAME}.
DATA_BASENAME=ifp-data
# Absolute parent directory under which the project is cloned. The final clone
# target is ${REPO_PARENT_PATH}/${PROJECT}.
REPO_PARENT_PATH=/Users/yuanchenxiang/openclaw-local-data

# ─── Local GitLab token pin ───────────────────────────────────────
# A runner may pin GITLAB_TOKEN here so the driven RUN_SINGLE_ISSUE path can
# authenticate without req_dispatcher carrying a secret in the trigger.
# Keep the committed value empty. Fill the real token only in the runner-local
# working tree or inject it through the execution environment.
GITLAB_TOKEN=
